Hight level api and javascript bindings to easy bidirectonal message passsing for nim and the webview .

Types

BindFn = proc (ctx: pointer; seqId: string; req: string) {.nimcall.}
DispatchFn = proc ()
Webview = object of RootObj
  impl: webview_t
  ptrs: seq[ptr WebviewContext]

webview_bind_fn = proc (seqId: cstring; req: cstring; arg: pointer)

WEBVIEW_HINT = enum
  WEBVIEW_HINT_NONE, WEBVIEW_HINT_MIN, WEBVIEW_HINT_MAX, WEBVIEW_HINT_FIXED

proc run(w: Webview): Webview {.discardable, ...raises: [], tags: [].}
Runs the main loop until it's terminated. After this function exits - you must destroy the webview. 
proc setHtml(w: Webview; html: string): Webview {.discardable, ...raises: [],

proc setTitle(w: Webview; title: string): Webview {.discardable, ...raises: [],
    tags: [].}
Updates the title of the native window. Must be called from the UI thread. 
proc terminate(w: Webview): Webview {.discardable, ...raises: [], tags: [].}
Stops the main loop. It is safe to call this function from another other background thread.
